      • search

        public SearchDataObjectResponse search(org.opengis.filter.Filter filter,
                                       int pageNumber,
                                       org.opengis.filter.expression.PropertyName[] properties,
                                       org.opengis.filter.sort.SortBy[] sortBy,
                                       boolean includeHidden)
                                throws CoalesceException
        Description copied from interface: ISearchClient
        Searches the DSS database.
        Specified by:
        search in interface ISearchClient
        Parameters:
        filter - OGC filter defining the constraints that can be checked against an instance of an object.
        pageNumber - sets the offset of the query. Each page is determined by ISearchClient.setPageSize(int).
        properties - is the list of properties (fields) that you wish to return as a part of your query. Property formatting follow the same rules as the filter "recordset name"."field name"; so if you wanted to return access scope this would be 'access_control_recordset.accessscope' or for DSS fields you can use CoalescePropertyFactory to get the properties.
        sortBy - is the list of properties (fields) that you wish to search on along with the direction. Property formatting follow the same rules as the filter "recordset name"."field name".
        includeHidden - if true then objects that have been hidden will be returned.
        Returns:
        the keys of objects that match the search criteria.
        Throws:
        CoalesceException
